diatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fwatch-fun-banter-and-a-sprint-race-between-shoaib-akhtar-harbhajan-singh%2Farticleshow%2F107840135.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20intense%20rivarly%20witnessed%20on%20the%20field%20between%20Shoaib%20Akhtar%20and%20Harbhajan%20Singh%20in%20their%20playing%20careers%20has%20been%20extensively%20chronicled%2C%20particularly%20in%20numerous%20India%20vs%20Pakistan%20matches%20throughout%20the%20years.%20However%2C%20the%20camaraderie%20they%20now%20share%20off%20the%20field%20as%20co-commentators%20is%20just%20as%20captivating%20for%20audiences%20worldwide.%20Some%20of%20those%20moments%20showed%20up%20in%20the%20latest%20vlog%20posted%20by%20Akhtar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fwatch-fun-banter-and-a-sprint-race-between-shoaib-akhtar-harbhajan-singh%2Farticleshow%2F107840135.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Government's%20Tryst%20with%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Should%20Neither%20Be%20Forgotten%20Nor%20Forgiven%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20094201%2FUntitled-design-15.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20bonds%20scheme%20has%20been%20declared%20illegal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20rare%20win%20in%20court%20for%20those%20resisting%20authoritarianism.%20But%20many%20elections%2C%20including%20the%20last%20general%20election%2C%20have%20been%20fought%20on%20these%20unlawful%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20have%20been%20appropriate%20to%20have%20heard%20and%20adjudicated%20on%20the%20issue%20earlier%20but%20the%20court%20chose%20not%20to%20do%20so.%20Former%20Chief%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20rewarded%20with%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20seat%2C%20when%20asked%20as%20to%20why%20he%20had%20delayed%20adjudicating%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20said%20he%20did%20not%20remember%20the%20issue%20coming%20up%20before%20his%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20will%20not%20know%20how%20diabolical%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20enterprise%20was%2C%20and%20it%20is%20for%20their%20benefit%20that%20this%20is%20being%20written.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20announced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20through%20the%202017%20Union%20Budget.%20The%20bonds%20would%20be%20a%20way%20for%20political%20parties%20to%20receive%20money%20through%20anonymous%20donors.%20The%20donor%20would%20have%20to%20reveal%20their%20identity%20to%20the%20bank%20while%20making%20the%20bond%20purchase%2C%20but%20the%20identity%20would%20not%20be%20revealed%20on%20the%20bond%20itself.%20Political%20parties%20could%20accept%20the%20money%20without%20being%20required%20to%20reveal%20who%20gave%20it.%20Voters%20would%20therefore%20not%20know%20who%20was%20funding%20and%20influencing%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20would%20allow%20foreign%20companies%20and%20even%20shell%20companies%20to%20donate%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20parties%20without%20having%20to%20inform%20anyone%20of%20the%20contribution%20or%20having%20their%20names%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20undid%20that%20part%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%2C%20under%20which%20corporates%20had%20to%20disclose%20details%20of%20their%20political%20donations%20in%20their%20annual%20statement%20of%20accounts.%20Now%20they%20were%20no%20longer%20required%20to%20do%20so.%20The%20corporates%20had%20earlier%20also%20been%20limited%20to%20donating%20a%20maximum%20of%207.5%25%20of%20their%20average%20three-year%20net%20profits%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20longer%2C%20because%20they%20could%20now%20just%20go%20through%20the%20electoral%20bond%20route%20as%20that%20cap%20had%20been%20lifted%20legally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20to%20fund%20a%20party%20anonymously%20was%20made%20easy.%20Bonds%20would%20be%20available%20in%20multiples%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20at%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20branches%20in%2029%20cities.%20A%20donor%20could%20purchase%20them%20through%20their%20bank%20account%20and%20hand%20them%20over%20to%20the%20party%20or%20individual%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20who%20could%20then%20encash%20them.%20They%20would%20be%20valid%20for%2015%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20days%20before%20the%202017%20Budget%2C%20a%20bureaucrat%20spotted%20it%20in%20finance%20minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%E2%80%99s%20speech%2C%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20assent%20was%20required%20for%20such%20a%20large%20shift.%20This%20was%20because%20the%20introduction%20of%20bonds%20required%20changes%20to%20the%20RBI%20Act%2C%20something%20that%20apparently%20the%20government%20did%20not%20know.%20The%20officer%20drafted%20a%20proposed%20amendment%20to%20align%20the%20RBI%20Act%20with%20the%20change%20and%20sent%20the%20file%20up%20the%20ranks%20for%20the%20finance%20minister%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20day%2C%20January%2028%2C%202017%2C%20a%20Saturday%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20sent%20a%20five-line%20email%20seeking%20its%20comments.%20The%20reply%20came%20the%20next%20working%20day%2C%20Monday%2C%20January%2030.%20The%20RBI%20said%20it%20was%20a%20bad%20idea%20because%20it%20went%20against%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20authority%20as%20the%20sole%20issuer%20of%20bearer%20instruments%2C%20meaning%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20bonds%2C%20because%20they%20were%20anonymous%2C%20could%20become%20currency%20and%20undermine%20the%20faith%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20point%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20unambiguous%3A%20amending%20the%20law%20to%20facilitate%20this%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20seriously%20undermine%20a%20core%20principle%20of%20central%20banking%20legislation%20and%20doing%20so%20would%20set%20a%20bad%20precedent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20second%20objection%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceven%20the%20intended%20purpose%20of%20the%20transparency%20might%20not%20be%20achievable%20as%20the%20original%20buyer%20of%20the%20instrument%20(the%20bond)%20need%20not%20be%20the%20actual%20contributor%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20person%20A%20purchased%20the%20bond%20and%20then%20sold%20it%2C%20at%20face%20value%20or%20more%2C%20to%20any%20entity%2C%20including%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%20that%20entity%20could%20gift%20it%20to%20a%20party.%20The%20nameless%20bond%20was%20as%20good%20as%20cash.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20bonds%20are%20bearer%20bonds%20and%20transferable%20by%20delivery%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20RBI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Chence%2C%20who%20finally%20and%20actually%20contributes%20the%20bond%20to%20the%20political%20party%20will%20not%20be%20known%E2%80%9D.%20This%20would%20affect%20the%20money%20laundering%20law%20as%20well%2C%20the%20RBI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20point%20it%20made%20was%20that%20what%20was%20being%20proposed%20through%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20the%20transfer%20of%20money%20from%20bank%20accounts%20of%20entities%20to%20political%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20could%20be%20done%20through%20a%20cheque%2C%20bank%20transfer%20or%20demand%20draft.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20special%20need%20for%2C%20or%20advantage%20by%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20Electoral%20Bearer%20Bond%2C%20that%20too%20by%20disturbing%20an%20established%20international%20practice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3Enext%20body%20to%20say%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20dangerous%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20Election%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20said%20that%20to%20exclude%20the%20reporting%20of%20donations%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20would%20have%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20repercussions%20on%20the%20transparency%20aspect%20of%20political%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EC%20remained%20opposed%20to%20the%20law%20even%20after%20it%20was%20enacted%20and%20continued%20to%20resist%20though%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20gave%20the%20government%20a%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20most%20important%20institutions%20related%20to%20the%20bonds%20tried%20to%20do%20their%20work%20and%20resisted%20the%20scheme.%20They%20were%20unable%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20RBI%20had%20responded%20immediately%2C%20one%20reason%20the%20government%20gave%20to%20dismiss%20its%20concern%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20advice%20has%20come%20quite%20late%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20is%20already%20printed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electoral%20bonds%20episode%20reveals%20the%20limits%20of%20institutional%20checks%20in%20our%20democracy.%20When%20a%20strong%20executive%20decides%20it%20wants%20something%2C%20even%20something%20that%20is%20dangerous%20and%20unconstitutional%2C%20there%20is%20little%20resistance%20from%20within%20to%20stop%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20now%20held%20that%20the%20scheme%20unconstitutional%2C%20something%20that%20was%20obvious%20to%20anyone%20familiar%20with%20the%20most%20basic%20details%20of%20what%20the%20bonds%20were%20for.%20But%20this%20should%20also%20alert%20us%20to%20how%20weak%20our%20institutions%20are%20and%20how%2C%20when%20they%20mean%20well%20for%20the%20country%2C%20they%20can%20just%20be%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAakar%20Patel%20is%20an%20author%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708404936000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20094201%2FUntitled-design-15.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-na