ewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08131855%2FScreenshot-2024-01-08-at-1.18.24%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Apart%20from%20extreme%20cold%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20winter%20is%20also%20notorious%20for%20bad%20air%20quality.%20During%20this%20season%2C%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20from%20farm%20fires%20in%20neighboring%20regions%20increases%20levels%20of%20pollutants%20in%20the%20city%2C%20amidst%20a%20decrease%20in%20wind%20speeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20winter%20of%202022-23%20was%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorthern%20India%20witnessed%20better%20air%20quality.%20Delhi%20showed%20a%2010%25%20improvement%20in%20its%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20(or%20PM2.5%2C%20as%20the%20air%20pollutant%20is%20known)%20levels.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20peninsular%20India%20%E2%80%93%20where%20air%20quality%20does%20not%20suffer%20in%20winters%20%E2%80%93%20recorded%20an%20increase%20in%20PM2.5%20levels%20during%20this%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20rare%20%E2%80%98triple%20dip%E2%80%99%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20event%20%E2%80%93%20three%20consecutive%20years%20of%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20conditions%2C%20driven%20by%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20caused%20this%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0048969724011021%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20February%2015%20has%20found%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fold.ptinews.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Frare-triple-dip-la-nina-behind-unusual-air-quality-trend-in-india-in-2022-23-study%2F747853.html%5C%22%3Enews%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERare%20%E2%80%98triple%20dip%E2%80%99%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20is%20a%20phase%20of%20the%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%20Southern%20Oscillation%20(ENSO)%2C%20a%20complex%20climate%20pattern%20that%20depends%20on%20fluctuating%20sea%20surface%20temperatures%20and%20atmospheric%20changes%20in%20the%20tropical%20Pacific%20Ocean.%20While%20weak%20monsoons%20and%20reduced%20rainfall%20in%20many%20regions%20(including%20most%20of%20south%20Asia)%20characterise%20an%20El%20Nin%CC%83o%20year%20that%20occurs%20when%20the%20tropical%20Pacific%20Ocean%20warms%20up%2C%20a%20contrasting%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20year%20is%20associated%20with%20cooler%20ocean%20waters%20in%20the%20tropical%20Pacific%20which%20often%20results%20in%20higher%20rainfall%20in%20some%20places.%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20years%2C%20therefore%2C%20can%20often%20be%20cooler%20and%20wetter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20rare%2C%20but%20the%20world%20just%20witnessed%20three%20back-to-back%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20years%20%E2%80%93%20or%20a%20%E2%80%98triple%20dip%E2%80%99%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20%E2%80%93%20from%202020%20to%202023.%20In%20May%20last%20year%2C%20the%20WMO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fel-nino-india-temperature-rainfall%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20streak%20had%20ended%20and%20that%20the%20world%20should%20prepare%20for%20the%20onset%20of%20an%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20retreat%20of%20the%20triple%20dip%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20coincided%20with%20the%20winter%20of%202022-23.%20And%20something%20extremely%20unusual%20happened%20at%20the%20same%20time%3A%20north%20India%2C%20which%20usually%20suffers%20from%20very%20poor%20air%20quality%20during%20the%20winter%20months%2C%20showed%20an%20improvement.%20The%20levels%20of%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20(PM2.5%2C%20an%20air%20pollutant%20that%20is%20released%20primarily%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels)%20here%20declined%20while%20compared%20to%20the%20average%20level%20of%20the%20recent%20past%20years%2C%20leading%20to%20fewer%20extreme%20pollution%20days.%20However%2C%20PM2.5%20levels%20in%20peninsular%20India%20%E2%80%93%20where%20air%20quality%20is%20usually%20not%20a%20concern%20%E2%80%93%20spiked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20why%2C%20a%20team%20of%20scientists%20led%20by%20Gufran%20Beig%2C%20chair%20professor%2C%20National%20Institute%20of%20Advanced%20Studies%2C%20studied%20levels%20of%20PM2.5%20in%20Indian%20cities%20during%20the%20three%20years%2C%20wind%20patterns%20and%20climatic%20changes.%20The%20team%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20sudden%20flip-flop%20of%20the%20current%20Indian%20pollution%20cycle%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20meteorological%20phenomenon%20which%20is%20linked%20to%20the%20final%20phase%20of%20triple%20dip%20La%20Nina%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20north%20India%2C%20Ghaziabad%20registered%20the%20most%20significant%20improvement%20with%20a%20reduction%20of%2033%25%20in%20its%20PM2.5%20levels%2C%20followed%20by%20Rohtak%20(30%25)%20and%20Noida%20(28%25).%20Delhi%20showed%20an%20improvement%20of%20around%2010%25.%20In%20peninsular%20India%2C%20however%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20good%20news.%20Mumbai%20recorded%20the%20highest%20deterioration%20in%20air%20quality%20with%20a%2030%25%20%3Cem%3Eincrease%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20PM2.5%20levels%2C%20followed%20by%20Coimbatore%20(28%25)%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Bengaluru%20(20%25)%20in%20Karnataka%20and%20Chennai%20(12%25)%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20large-scale%20wind%20patterns%20were%20key%20here%2C%20per%20the%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Cem%3EScience%20of%20the%20Total%20Environment%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Slower%20winds%20near%20the%20surface%20in%20peninsular%20India%20trapped%20pollutants%20and%20concentrated%20PM2.5%20levels%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20contrast%2C%20too%20feeble%20western%20disturbances%2C%20and%20unique%20wind%20patterns%20with%20the%20absence%20of%20rain%20and%20clouds%20and%20faster%20ventilation%20led%20to%20a%20significant%20improvement%20in%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20North%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20findings%20are%20vindicated%20as%20the%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20winter%20of%202023-24%2C%20when%20La%20Nina%20ended%2C%20returned%20to%20normal%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20lead%20author%20Beig%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERole%20of%20climate%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELa%20Ni%C3%B1a%20events%20do%20not%20usually%20continue%20for%20three%20years%20in%20succession%3B%20climate%20change%20caused%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20winter%20of%202022-23%20coincided%20with%20the%20last%20phase%20of%20an%20unusual%20triple-dip%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20event%2C%20the%20first%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%E2%80%9D%20R.H.%20Kripalani%2C%20a%20climate%20scientist%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Tropical%20Meteorology%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20PTI.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20phenomenon%2C%20influenced%20by%20climate%20change%2C%20impacted%20the%20large-scale%20wind%20pattern%2C%20playing%20a%20decisive%20role%20in%20preventing%20stagnation%20conditions%20in%20north%20Indian%20cities%20and%20thus%20improving%20air%20quality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20it%20led%20to%20calmer%20conditions%20in%20peninsular%20Indian%20cities%2C%20accelerating%20transboundary%20pollution%20and%20significantly%20deteriorating%20air%20quality%2C%20he%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20study%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmodulated%20large-scale%20wind%20patterns%20linked%20to%20climatic%20changes%20may%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20even%20at%20a%20local%20scale%20leading%20to%20unusual%20changes%20in%20the%20distribution%20of%20air%20pollutants%2C%20suggesting%20ever-stringent%20emission%20control%20actions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708402852000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F08131855%2FScreenshot-2024-01-08-at-1.18.24%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fair-quality-improved-in-north-india-fell-in-peninsula-in-2022-winter-due-to-rare-triple-dip-la-nina-event-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rare%20%E2%80%98triple%20dip%E2%80%99%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20event%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20three%20consecutive%20years%20of%20La%20Ni%C3%B1a%20conditions%20%E2%80%93%20was%20caused%20by%20climate%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fair-quality-improved-in-north-india-fell-in-peninsula-in-2022-winter-due-to-rare-triple-dip-la-nina-event-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RGV%20says%20he%20does%20not%20follow%20any%20religion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708402406000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107839118%2Cimgsize-30952.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fram-gopal-varma-reveals-he-follows-only-this-thing-and-not-morals-or-religion%2Farticleshow%2F107839014.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107839014.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERenowned%20director%20Ram%20Gopal%20Varma%20reflects%20on%20his%20rebellious%20nature%2C%20tracing%20it%20back%20to%20a%20Marxist%20interpretation%20of%20Ramayana%20during%20his%20schooling.%20In%20a%20candid%20interview%2C%20he%20rejects%20morality%20and%20religion%20but%20advocates%20for%20following%20the%20law.%20Varma%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%20in%20cinema%2C%20challenging%20societal%20norms%20and%20promoting%20critical%20thinking.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fram-gopal-varma-reveals-he-follows-only-this-thing-and-not-morals-or-religion%2Farticleshow%2F107839014.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20diesel%20fl