0is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Hayden%20Rue%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20expat%20who's%20lived%20in%20Nepal%20since%202016.%20This%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Salem%2C%20Oregon.%20Growing%20up%2C%20my%20family%20and%20I%20didn't%20venture%20far%20from%20the%20West%20Coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20gardener%20for%20several%20older%20couples.%20One%20of%20my%20clients%20recommended%20that%20I%20consider%20joining%20the%20Peace%20Corps%2C%20a%20US%20government%20agency%20that%20assists%20developing%20countries.%20I%20was%20in%20my%20early%2020s%20and%20didn't%20have%20a%20set%20plan%20for%20a%20career%20at%20the%20time%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20and%20a%20half%20later%2C%20I%20got%20an%20email%20informing%20me%20that%20I%20had%20been%20chosen%20for%20a%20deployment%20to%20Nepal%2C%20and%20would%20be%20spending%2027%20months%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20seven%20years%2C%20I've%20worked%20as%20a%20project%20coordinator%20for%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20international%20NGOs%2C%20and%20charities%20in%20Nepal.%20I%20also%20run%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhaydenrue.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20reading%20to%20children%20in%20nepal.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb13936fcb546d2d4eeb4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHayden%20Rue%20in%20Lumbini%20with%20World%20Bank%20Project.%3Cp%3EHayden%20Rue%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EOrganized%20chaos%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20organized%20chaos%20to%20Nepal.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20stepped%20out%20of%20the%20airport%20when%20I%20first%20arrived%2C%20car%20horns%20were%20blaring.%20Dozens%20of%20taxi%20drivers%20approached%20me%2C%20each%20promising%20to%20offer%20the%20lowest%20price%20for%20a%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20a%20mixture%20of%20fear%20and%20amazement%20as%20I%20drove%20down%20the%20narrow%20streets%20flanked%20by%20seemingly%20never-ending%20buildings%20that%20were%20connected%20by%20countless%20telephone%20wires.%20Large%20crowds%20of%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20animals%20%E2%80%94%20crossed%20the%20street%20in%20every%20direction%20while%20dodging%20traffic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222950%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20overlooking%20patan%20durbar%20in%20nepal.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb19bf94aa8ee8e84a8110%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHayden%20Rue%20in%20Patan%20Durbar%20Square.%3Cp%3EHayden%20Rue%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ESteep%20learning%20curve%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENepal%20is%20a%20challenging%20country%20to%20live%20in%20if%20you%20are%20not%20ready%20for%20constant%20uncertainty.%20There%20is%20a%20steep%20learning%20curve%20when%20visiting%20Nepal%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20over%20a%20year%20living%20in%20Kathmandu%2C%20the%20capital%2C%20where%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20get%20any%20sort%20of%20peace%20and%20quiet.%20Even%20though%20it's%20a%20big%20city%2C%20it%20felt%20suffocating%20at%20times%20as%20I%20had%20barely%20any%20personal%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20renting%20a%20flat%20where%20the%20owners%20lived%20downstairs.%20The%20owners%20saw%20me%20as%20a%20son%20and%20treated%20me%20like%20I%20was%20a%20part%20of%20their%20family.%20While%20this%20was%20initially%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20it%20eventually%20went%20overboard.%20She%20would%20come%20into%20my%20flat%20unannounced.%20I%20also%20had%20to%20do%20jobs%20around%20the%20house%2C%20including%20climbing%20into%20a%201%2C000-liter%20water%20tank%20and%20cleaning%20the%20inside%20by%20hand%20with%20steel%20wool%20and%20sponges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20overlooking%20the%20valleys%20in%20kathmandu.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb13926fcb546d2d4eeb4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHayden%20Rue%20lived%20in%20Kathmandu%20Valley%20when%20he%20first%20moved%20to%20Nepal.%3Cp%3EHayden%20Rue%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20crossing%20the%20road%20can%20be%20challenging%20for%20the%20uninitiated%20in%20Nepal.%20Car%20crashes%20are%20common.%20There%20are%20usually%20no%20crosswalks%2C%20so%20cars%20and%20scooters%20do%20not%20stop%20for%20pedestrians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20several%20of%20my%20friends%20from%20the%20US%20visited%20Kathmandu%20and%20were%20glued%20to%20the%20sidewalk%20in%20fear%2C%20terrified%20to%20cross%20the%20road.%20I%20had%20to%20quickly%20zig-zag%20through%20traffic%20and%20lead%20them%20to%20the%20other%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInfrastructure%20isn't%20well%20developed%20in%20Nepal.%20Taking%20bus%20rides%20from%20Pokhara%20to%20Kathmandu%2C%20which%20are%20about%20200%20kilometers%20apart%2C%20could%20take%2015%20hours%20due%20to%20accidents%20on%20the%20two-lane%20highway.%20When%20I%20lived%20in%20the%20small%20village%20of%20Syangja%2C%20there%20wasn't%20any%20electricity%20for%20two%20weeks.%20The%20single%20power%20pole%20connecting%20all%20the%20houses%20was%20damaged.%20This%20meant%20dinners%20in%20the%20dark%2C%20no%20TV%2C%20no%20way%20to%20charge%20anything%2C%20and%20nothing%20to%20do%20but%20talk%20after%20sunset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20much%20cheaper%20than%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20monthly%20rent%20for%20the%20flat%20in%20Syangja%20was%20around%208%2C000%20Nepalese%20Rupees%2C%20or%20%2460.%20In%20Kathmandu%2C%20I%20paid%20around%20double%20the%20price.%20In%20Pokhara%20%E2%80%94%20the%20second-largest%20city%20in%20Nepal%20%E2%80%94%20I%20paid%20around%20%24210%20in%20monthly%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20I%20spend%20around%20%24600%20a%20month%20and%20live%20a%20comfortable%20life%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that's%20surprisingly%20costly%20in%20Nepal%20is%20groceries.%20I%20usually%20spend%20between%20%24225%20and%20%24300%20on%20groceries%20a%20month%20as%20processed%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20like%20chocolate%2C%20dairy%20products%2C%20and%20soda%20%E2%80%94%20have%20to%20be%20imported%20and%20are%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20on%20a%20swing%20overlooking%20the%20himalayas%20in%20nepal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb19e794aa8ee8e84a8117%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221228%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHayden%20Rue%20at%20Khumai%20Danda%20Trek%2C%3Cp%3EHayden%20Rue%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20slower%20pace%20of%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20rewarding%20part%20about%20living%20in%20Nepal%20is%20the%20connections%20you%20make%20with%20people.%20Time%20is%20slower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20currently%20traveling%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20I%20plan%20to%20return%20to%20Nepal%20in%20August%2C%20where%20I%20hope%20to%20open%20a%20small%20cafe%20in%20Pokhara%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20friends%20and%20family%20continue%20to%20tell%20me%20to%20come%20home%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20myself%20moving%20back%20anytime%20soon.%20In%20Nepal%2C%20you%20can%20connect%20with%20others%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20are%20from%2C%20or%20what%20they%20have%20planned%20for%20the%20day.%20I%20could%20sit%20for%20hours%20drinking%20tea%20and%20talking%20to%20people%20about%20their%20lives%2C%20experiences%2C%20and%20dreams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-expat-life-abroad-nepal-blackout-infrastructure-ph