he%20resignation%20of%20K.S.%20Eshwarappa%2C%20the%20then%20minister%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20Justice%20P.K.%20Mishra%2C%20however%2C%20refused%20to%20quash%20the%20criminal%20case%20against%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20Congress%20general%20secretary%20and%20Karnataka%20in-charge%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%2C%20state%20ministers%20M.B.%20Patil%20and%20Ramalinga%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%2C%20however%2C%20stayed%20a%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20order%2C%20which%20had%20imposed%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20each%20on%20the%20accused%20and%20had%20directed%20them%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20special%20court%20on%20March%206.%20The%20top%20court%2C%20however%2C%20issued%20notices%20to%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20and%20the%20complainant%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIssue%20notice%2C%20returnable%20in%20six%20weeks%2C%20Till%20further%20orders%2C%20%5Bthere%20shall%20be%20a%5D%20stay%20of%20proceedings%20and%20impugned%20order%20%5Bof%20Karnataka%20High%20Court%5D%20against%20the%20petitioners%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-stays-proceedings-case-against-karnataka-cm-siddaramaiah-2022-protest-march%5C%22%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20dates%20back%20to%20February%202022%2C%20when%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20others%20were%20detained%20for%20holding%20a%20protest%20to%20demand%20the%20resignation%20and%20arrest%20of%20Eshwarappa%2C%20following%20the%20death%20by%20suicide%20of%20contractor%20Santosh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocates%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20Devadatt%20Kamat%2C%20and%20Siddharth%20Luthra%20appeared%20for%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Singhvi%2C%20the%20criminal%20case%20was%20registered%20for%20exercising%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20and%20is%20totally%20against%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20under%20Article%2019%20(1)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20Justice%20Mishra%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20the%20offences%20which%20have%20been%20invoked%20in%20the%20case%20have%20been%20kept%20in%20the%20statute%20books%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20reasonable%20restrictions%20under%20the%20fundamental%20rights.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CElse%20whatever%20disturbances%20are%20there%20on%20roads%2C%20we%20have%20to%20quash.%20Your%20argument%20is%20%E2%80%A6%20politicians%20do%20it%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20quashed%3F%E2%80%9D%20Mishra%20retorted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20then%20went%20on%20to%20ask%20if%20permission%20had%20been%20sought%20for%20the%20demonstration.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20cannot%20go%20one%20fine%20morning%20and%20assemble%20in%20thousands%2C%20and%20%5Bthen%5D%20says%20nothing%20can%20happen%20to%20us%20because%20we%20are%20protesting%E2%80%A6%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Sibal%20said%20that%20law%20and%20order%20cannot%20be%20a%20ground%20to%20deny%20a%20fundamental%20right.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20constitutional%20right%2C%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20added%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Siddarmaiah%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20in%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20none%20of%20the%20offences%20mentioned%20in%20Section%20141%20(unlawful%20assembly)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20are%20met.%20It%20also%20added%20that%20no%20violence%20stemmed%20out%20of%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708343977000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18164526%2FFwBN2HcakAEGvBw.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-proceedings-against-siddaramaiah-others-in-the-2022-protes